# Code Style

## TypeScript

- Strict mode, no `any` unless truly unavoidable (comment why)
- Prefer `type` over `interface` for object shapes
- Named exports, no default exports (except Next.js pages/layouts)
- Use `const` by default, `let` only when reassignment is needed

## React / Next.js

- Functional components only
- Server Components by default; add `'use client'` only when needed
- Colocate styles: `ComponentName.module.scss` next to `index.tsx`
- Props type defined above the component in the same file

```tsx
type AccordionProps = {
  items: AccordionItem[]
  locale: Locale
}

export const Accordion = ({ items, locale }: AccordionProps) => {
  // ...
}
```

## Imports

Sorted by `@trivago/prettier-plugin-sort-imports` — don't reorder manually.

## Comments

- English only
- Don't state the obvious — comment *why*, not *what*
- No commented-out code in commits

## Error Handling

- Always handle fetch errors with meaningful fallbacks
- Log errors server-side, show user-friendly messages client-side
